Project Management tool
Handles verification, package building, installment.
-> Build generation
-> Dependency Resolution
-> Documentation
-- Uses POM(Project Object Model) to achieve this
-- When given maven commadn it looks at  pom.xml file of current directory and get needed config

Parts of Maven:
- XML Schema
- Parent -used to define parent project
- Properties - for configuration
- Dependencies - all dependencies related to the repo

Sequential execution flow
Validation of project structure
Compile Source code
Tests Run
Package to JAR/WAR
VerifyIntegrity of package
Install package to local repo
